	   <tr><td colspan=2>Rangers really got a boost in soloing capability with Panic Animal, Ive found.&nbsp;&nbsp;I solo'd Griffennes in North Karana at 30th level, and Im soloing Cougars in Iceclad Ocean now at 31 and 32.  Experience in Iceclad is great, and Ive managed to get 2 cougar claw earrings, so far.<br><br>Iceclad Method Ive Used:<br><br>From the dock, if you take a slight right, you'll find three Gnomes sitting near a tree.  The nearest tree to the left of this has a three-spawn of cougars that dont move.  Find 'em!<br><br>Harmony the group of three cougars.  Snare-pull one and get some distance from her.  Then, DOT her, and hit her with a few arrows while making your way back to the dock.  Once there, keep up the arrows until shes pretty close (you'll learn the best timing for you with practise) and then throw Panic Animal on her.  Begin slashing with preferred melee method.  Thank you, drive through.<br><br>Keep an eye on your snare and fear, though.  When they drop, be ready to recast quick.  Its possible to fight a blue con'd cougar with almost no health loss at level 31, but you have to pay close attention to what spells are sticking on your target.  If your careless, the nearest bind point is Thurgardin, which is a pretty long walk of shame.  White con'd Cougars will whack you for good damage consistently, but again, stay on your game and you'll be dropping them for full blue bubs a kill :)  <br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Quorrin Halfhand<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
